[2019-02-22 16:33:56 UTC] woolfus: @A_Seagull It's typically not too important to focus specifically on sugar if you're not diabetic, but things like glycemic load do exist. Essentially, different foods are converted to sugars at different rates in the body. A food that quickly converts into sugars puts greater demand on your body to respond quickly and efficiently with insulin, etc. Again, not too bad for healthy people but less of a known quantity in diabetic/insulin resistant people.
